    "The detailed groups of questions are presented in Table 2.",
    "The judgments of LLMs (bystanders) on multiple situations involving the perpetrator and the victim, as well as the experimenter's judgments on the speech acts of LLMs, can be categorized into four levels of testing:",
    "Test 1.0 evaluates LLMs' performance on ethical judgments of harm-based initial scenarios. 2.",
    "Test 2.0 assesses their performance on ethical judgments in complex scenarios with multiple variables derived from the initial scenarios. 3.",
    "Test 3.0 examines their performance on judgments of controversial or complex, unsolvable moral dilemmas. 4."
